      "level": {
        "value": 17
      },
      "disable": "<p>@Check[type:thievery|dc:35] (master) to wrap the gem without touching it, or dispel magic (9th level, counteract DC 38) to counteract the effect on the gem.</p>",
      "description": "<p>An immense sapphire that attempts to trap the soul of whomever touches it.</p><hr /><h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p>Ileosa spent a scroll of <em>trap the soul</em> (trigger-object) on this stone, keying it to <strong>one named PC</strong> — the bearer of @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-items.Item.serithtialSword1]{Serithtial}, or whoever she hates most. The sapphire is a 20,000 gp stone in PF1e terms (re-scale ~2,000 gp). The @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.immortalIchor001]{ichor} — and @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.ithierGylou00001]{Ithier} — try to <em>charm or dominate</em> the named PC into picking it up.</p>",
