  "items": [
    {
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Reaction.webp",
      "name": "Trap the Soul",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature touches the gem</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The creature must attempt a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:38] save as the gem attempts to trap its soul</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes [[/r {6d8}[negative]]]{6d8 negative damage} and becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Drained]{Drained 2} and @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Doomed]{Doomed 2}.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature's body becomes lifeless as its soul is drawn into the gem. While the soul is in the gem, the target can't be returned to life through any means, even powerful magic such as wish. If the gem is destroyed or magic has successfully counteracted the gem, the soul is freed and may be resurrected.</p>"
        },
